Class Cell

java.lang.Object
Cell
All Implemented Interfaces:

Direct Known Subclasses:

public class Cell
extends Object
implements Comparable<Cell>
Base class that also acts as the Empty cell type.

    • compareTo

      public int compareTo​(Cell other)
      This method is the implementation of the interface Comparable which allows the cells to be compared to one another even if they are different types. As implemented, empty cells are "less than" TextCell, DateCell and NumberCell.

      One should override this implementation in the derived classes to get proper sorting. Use "public int compareTo(Cell other)" when overriding.

      Collections.sort(arr) will sort arr of type ArrayList.

      Collections.sort(arr, Collections.reverseOrder()) will sort it in reverse.

      The sort order is:

      • empty
      • numbers
      • dates
      • text
      Specified by:
      compareTo in interface Comparable<Cell>
      Parameters:
      other - is the cell to which this cell is being compared to.
      Returns:
      -1 if this cell is less than the other cell. 0 if equal. 1 if greater than.
